* Task 6 fixture (dup-name case): COMMON/CALLER2.NSP
* Proves that order matters: SAME module name, SAME CALLNAT statement,
* but different current library → different winner.
* This caller's current library is COMMON (path prefix match).
* When CALLNAT 'SHARED' is resolved:
* - Current library COMMON → has SHARED.NSN
* - Expected: resolves to COMMON/SHARED.NSN (different from APP/CALLER.NSP!)
*
* OQ-3, OQ-5: current library determines the chain start.
* FR-16, FR-5: M-3 NFR-7 test case — order changes the resolved target.

DEFINE DATA
LOCAL
  1 RESULT (A10)
END DEFINE

* Call to SHARED from COMMON — should resolve to COMMON/SHARED.NSN
* (even though both modules have the same name, current library determines winner)
CALLNAT 'SHARED'

MOVE 'OK' TO RESULT

END
